2026-04-12: CloudWatch centralized logging, Prometheus metrics, PagerDuty alerting
  - Structured JSON logging (timestamp, level, service, user_id, duration_ms, error) prevents brittle parsing
  - Log retention: 7 days debug, 30 days errors/warnings; metrics track p50/p95/p99 latency, throughput, error rates
  - Alert thresholds: P99 latency > 2s, error rate > 1%, memory > 85% (auto-scale), DB CPU > 75% (manual review)
  - X-Request-ID propagated through microservices; sampled tracing (1%) in CloudWatch Insights for latency investigation
  - Dashboards: service health (green/amber/red), user journey (signup funnel), SLA compliance (99.5%), cost per service
  - On-call rotation: 1-week shifts, single engineer, escalation > 1hr; quarterly threshold tuning prevents alert fatigue
